<task id="WKSP-041" project="spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build wizard Step 1: Choose Layout Template</title>
    <phase>5</phase>
    <tags>frontend, fluent-ui, code-page</tags>
    <estimated-effort>5h</estimated-effort>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <dependencies>002, 040</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>D</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <role>Senior developer implementing workspace personalization</role>
    <goal>Build the first wizard step where users choose from 6 layout templates, each displayed as a visual card with grid thumbnail, name, and slot count.</goal>
    <context>
      The Layout Wizard is a 3-step dialog (template -> sections -> arrange). Step 1 presents the
      available layout templates defined in the LAYOUT_TEMPLATES constant (Task 002). Each template
      specifies a grid structure (rows, columns, slot count) and has a human-friendly name.

      Users select one template to define the structural grid for their workspace. The selected template
      is highlighted. The wizard shell (header, step navigation, cancel button) comes from the shared
      WizardDialog component in @spaarke/ui-components.

      In edit mode, the template matching the existing layout is pre-selected. In create mode, no
      template is selected initially.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - MUST use WizardDialog from @spaarke/ui-components for wizard shell (header, navigation, cancel)
      - MUST display 6 template cards in a responsive grid (2-3 columns depending on width)
      - Each card MUST show: visual grid thumbnail (SVG or CSS grid preview), template name, slot count
      - Selected card MUST be visually highlighted (Fluent v9 selection pattern)
      - MUST use Fluent UI v9 components exclusively (Card, Text, Badge) per ADR-021
      - "Next" button MUST be disabled until a template is selected
      - In edit mode, pre-select the template matching the current layout's grid structure
      - MUST support dark mode via Fluent design tokens
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/solutions/WorkspaceLayoutWizard/src/</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WizardShell/</file>
  </relevant-files>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read the WizardDialog component from shared library to understand its API: steps definition, activeStep, onNext, onBack, onCancel props.</step>
    <step id="2">Create a TemplateCard component that renders a single template option: CSS grid thumbnail showing the slot structure, template name (Text), and slot count (Badge).</step>
    <step id="3">Build CSS grid thumbnails for each of the 6 templates — use small div grids with Fluent design token colors to visually represent the layout structure (e.g., 2-column shows two equal boxes, sidebar shows narrow+wide).</step>
    <step id="4">Create the TemplateSelectionStep component that renders a responsive grid of 6 TemplateCards. Track selectedTemplateId in local state.</step>
    <step id="5">Add selection styling: selected card gets a highlighted border using Fluent v9 tokens (colorBrandStroke1), unselected cards use subtle border (colorNeutralStroke1).</step>
    <step id="6">Wire into WizardDialog: configure step 1 with this component, disable "Next" until selectedTemplateId is set, pass selected template to parent wizard state on navigation.</step>
    <step id="7">Handle edit mode: if wizard receives an existing layout, pre-select the matching template based on grid structure comparison.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>6 template cards are displayed in a responsive grid with visual grid thumbnails</criterion>
    <criterion>Clicking a card selects it with a visible highlight (brand color border)</criterion>
    <criterion>"Next" button is disabled until a template is selected</criterion>
    <criterion>In edit mode, the template matching the existing layout is pre-selected</criterion>
    <criterion>Component renders correctly in both light and dark Fluent themes</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
